defaultWritten evidence submitted by the Legal Aid Practitioners Group (JRR 0035)defaultThe Legal Aid Practitioners Group is a membership organisation for firms and organ
defaultisations with a contract to carry out legal aid work. Our members are based throughout England and Wales and are both private practices and not for profit organisations. Our members carry out civil and criminal work and cover the whole range of sizes from 
defaultsmall sole principal firms to some of the largest providers of legal aid services in the country. 
