default2. LAPG notes that the Government’s latest proposals to 
defaultmake changes to judicial review are at variance with assurances made by Ministers to Parliament during the passage of the LASPO Act 2012 regarding the continued availability of legal aid for judicial review post-LASPO. For example, Ken Clarke gave an assur
defaultance that the Government would be “continuing legal aid in all cases involving judicial review”, and added that the Government “do not think that the Government or any public body should be resisting a claim about abuse of their powers from a litigant who 
defaultcannot get legal advice” (Programme (No 3) motion, House of Commons, 17 April 2012, 
defaultcol
default 227). The Civil Legal Aid (Merits) Regulations 2012 issued under LASPO Act provided a more robust test for availability of legal aid for judicial review cases and has a
defaultlready restricted the availability of public funding.
